## Note on LGPL-3.0 Libraries (pystray, PySide6)

pystray and PySide6 are used as unmodified libraries installed via pip.
Per LGPL-3.0 §4, users can replace these libraries by reinstalling
alternative versions via `pip install` or `uv pip install`. The application
does not statically link or modify these libraries.

## Note on PyInstaller (GPL-2.0)

PyInstaller is used only during the build process to package the application.
The PyInstaller bootloader has a special exception that allows distribution
of the packaged application under any license. PyInstaller itself is not
distributed with the application binary.
